<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8243333>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Morphologically comparison of Ophiorrhiza macrocarpa and O. napoensis. A–C: Ophiorrhiza macrocarpa. A & B: Inflorescence, C: Stipule. D–I: Ophiorrhiza napoensis. D: Habit, E: Inflorescence, F: Longitudinally dissected long-styled flower, G: Longitudinally dissected short-styled flower, H: Inflorescence in top view, I: Stipule. Scales C & I=5 mm, A, E, F, G & H=1 cm. (Photos taken by L. Wu)" ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8243333/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

